        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "Interpretation and conclusion\n- In aqueous solution, Cu(II) (a borderline hard acid) generally binds chloride a bit more strongly than bromide, whereas the opposite trend is more typical for Cu(I). This is the expected HSAB trend and is consistent with the SRD‑46 coverage for these systems.\n- I intended to pull matched‑condition log K1 values at 25 °C (nitrate/perchlorate media) for a side‑by‑side table, but the time budget cut off the value fetch. If you’d like, I can retrieve specific log K1 (and, if needed, log K2/β2) under identical conditions so we can quantify the difference.",
